tips.text: Had drinks here with friends & the bar accommodates walk-ins best. Good plates of small bites / asian tapas. Try their version of the bloody mary - that one was really good.
Much more affordable than Burnt Ends their sister restaurant
Squid Ink Tonnarelli is to die for!!!

tips.text: The egg was cooked to perfection! Place closes at 7.30pm!
party of 5 could not finish tomahawk wagyu. brought giant bone home for flintstones cosplay. bam bam! uni pasta = good but karaage and cold truffle potato = average.
From the folks who brought you Ronin and The Plain; try the drumlets, the fish & chips and the off menu desserts. Just 5 days old but steady showing so much potential. The coffee is also exemplary.
Kenyen!! 
It's very good (I wouldn't call it "amazingly good") but I still prefer my Adam Road NL.
This is one of the best kept secrets in Singapore, they have a great champagne selection and one the best cold cuts and cheese platters in town.
Ohhh the cakes are sooo good. Reasonable priced too.
Tasty and good value omakase if you don't mind early 6pm seating. Will be back.
Superb Italian fare
Wong Ah Yoke (food critic) likes: Breaded Kaffir Lime Fresh Oysters, Roasted US Bay Scallop, Grain-fed US Holstein Ribeye 365 Days, Spiced Deboned Red Snapper. Source: Sunday Times
Reasonable price with good food. Nice to enjoy the mood of korea
The cheese selection is phenomenal. Nice place to reminisce summer in Paris!
Love the Vintage decor. Try the Ungai Benedict for Brunch.
Sashimi rice bowl was yum!
Best Italian food in Singapore!

venue.name: Ya Kun Kaya Toast 亞坤

tips.text: 본점이지만 소박한 느낌이 좋은 이곳에서 토스트 4조각과 계란 2개, 커피로 구성된 토스트 Set 는 4싱가폴$ 로 토스트를 계란에 찍어서 커피와 함께 먹으면 달콤하고 진한 맛이 배가된다...
Other places should learn from these guys. Few things done to perfection. Service was excellent. Attentive staff.
Best korean restaurant that I've been to along Amoy street. Weekday set lunches are $12 and delicious!!! Also, free seaweed 😆
The seasoned meat are tasty as compared to the grilled ones. They used traditional charcoal for barbecuing.
Just tried the crème caramel maison and the dame blanche, it was yummy ! (Tested and approved by a genuine French girl !)
Awesome squid-ink pasta, gotta try it!
From kaiseiki, they have changed to a la carte japanese restaurant. Quality of food is still stand out. Sashimi platter was pure joy to eat, grilled onigiri had homemade taste & somen was refreshing.
Good healthy food for good price. Love the hummus with falafel.
This is the best place to take a break and chill out with their awesome muffins + coffee + wifi. Please ask yourselves why you aren't here.
We enjoyed great service, delicious food and generous portions. The array of mozzarella on offer to start should not be missed, especially the burrata. Save some room for a sensational tiramisu!
Here is the menu!
Try the tasting menu. Spicy octopus dish followed by slightly sweet duck was high gastronomy. Lively atmosphere with music and open kitchen.
Really nice drinks. Try the kingfish sashimi and the fantastic bahru boot leg. Sit at the bar because the staff is really nice!
One of the better Chirashi Don I've tried. I like the flavoured rice and the Alaskan Crab Stick. 👍🏻 #howtonotbefat #jin
Definitively the best salad I ever eat
What a great find. Feels like in Australia. Wholesome food with an easy vibe. For something light, don't miss the quinoa salad or the granola yogurt. For something heavier, try the smoked mackerel!
Drinks time every Friday and Saturday night 10.30pm - 1am!
Great open air views of Boat Quay. Cocktails are not too bad, the Cuba cocktail slips down very nicely.

formattedAddress: Lv 1, Park Regis Hotel (23 Merchant Rd.)

tips.text: Dinner with colleagues. I'm thrilled to try their Steamed Live Marble Goby. 😘😊
Calamari: If u think this is u typical deep-fried version, consider again. It is really char-grilled (4 a change) & surprisingly tasty. Recommended!
You will see the whole family. Spot their son and daughter: The T-ara and SHINee lookalikes.
Sooooo gooood
Piedra Negra still the best mexican in town. The portions here are really small, tapas stile. They have no burritos, tacos are average and for a Mexican 'street food' this place is pricey.
Beef rague papadelle aka beef pasta
Affordable authentic Japanese bar food. We had delicious sashimi and kushiyaki accompanied by a couple of draft Sapporo and went home satisfied and not-broke.
Grilled fig and goat cheese bruschetta is good!

tips.text: I love this place. Not sure what the other dude is talking about but portion sizes are huge. I usually get a wrap for lunch and take half of it takeaway and eat it for dinner its so generous. Big ups!

Healthy food and taste delicious.
would go back again for the delectable crab croquettes &, shakshouka. I'd also recommend the Merlot by the glass or Malbec. lovely service & ambience. make sure to book!
